import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['ret'] = pd.to_numeric(data['ret'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='ret', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['ret'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='open', y='close', data=data)
    chart.set(title='What is the correlation between open and close prices?')
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='date', y='signal', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['signal'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median signal: {:.2f}'.format(data['signal'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of the signal over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='variable', y='value', data=pd.melt(data[['high', 'low']]), ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily highs and lows?')
    ax.axhline(y=data['high'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median High: {data["high"].median():.2f}')
    ax.axhline(y=data['low'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Low: {data["low"].median():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
